This paper deals with an online scheduling problem, which is a classic topic in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves making decisions based on incomplete information, which is a common theme in machine learning and information theory (cs.IT, cs.LG). The proposed algorithms involve making decisions based on maximizing a value function, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the problem involves scheduling jobs on a single machine, which is a classic problem in control theory (cs.SY).
